    "title": "Apollo Tyres is Hiring: Quality Control Engineer (Senior)",
    "description": "Are you a skilled Quality Control Engineer looking for your next big career move? Apollo Tyres in Bengaluru offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout Apollo Tyres:\nApollo Tyres is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Apollo Tyres!",
